<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; color:#000000; bEditID:r3st1; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; "><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#000066" size="6">{!Contact.SchoolText__c}</font></span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="'Times New Roman', Times, serif" color="#ff6600" size="4"><i>Chartered By The British Schools Foundation</i></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif" color="#c0c0c0" size="6"><b><i><br></i></b></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><font style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);" face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></div><div style="text-align: left;"><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif" size="4"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px;">Dear&nbsp;{!Contact.Salutation} {!Contact.LastName},</span></font></div><div>
<p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><span class="s1">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">I would like to welcome you all back from the Easter break and hope you all had a relaxing time. We can now look forward to a busy term 3 that includes our Year 6 Standardised Assessment Tests (SATs).</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">&nbsp;</font><span style="font-size: 12pt;">At BSKL, we run a literacy-based thematic curriculum, which we hope will really engage the children in their learning. &nbsp;Our main theme this term is </span><b style="font-size: 12pt;">Propaganda</b><span style="font-size: 12pt;">.&nbsp;</span></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255); font-size: 12pt;">English</b></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">In English this term, we will be focusing on the use of commas, clauses, pronouns, word classes, prefixes and suffixes, conjunctions and &nbsp;prepositions in our grammar lessons. During writing, we will be looking at non-chronological reports. We will be studying the features of these reports and using talk for writing to make text maps. Finally, the children will write their own non-chronological report on an animal of their choice. We will also be looking at classic fiction, including the Just William series. &nbsp;For poetry we will be looking at poems focusing on imagery and description. This includes how to use language to evoke feelings and produce impressions.</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255); font-size: 12pt;">Mathematics</b></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">The children will have five hours of mathematics lessons each week, ensuring that all aspects of the mathematics curriculum are covered. We will be using the new <i>Mathematics Mastery</i> approach to ensure that the children achieve a deep understanding of the concepts they are learning. We will be focusing this term on Venn and Carroll diagrams and interpreting graphs. We will also be looking at timetables and calendars. After this we will be recapping on the four main operations; multiplication, division, addition and subtraction and looking at fractions, decimals and percentages and shape, space and measure.</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255); font-size: 12pt;">Science</b></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">In science, we will be carrying on with 'animals including humans’ and then looking at classification. This will involve looking at circulation and the work done by Galen and Harvey, the lungs and how they function, blood and its purpose in the human body and how to keep healthy and lead a healthy lifestyle. &nbsp;For classification the children will study how living things are classified into broad groups. We will also look at microorganisms, how these are grouped and finally the children will try and identify creatures using classification keys.</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255); font-size: 12pt;">Integrated Curriculum (Topic)</b></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">This term we will be looking at propaganda and its role in history. &nbsp;The children will be looking at how propaganda has been used in the past and the effect it has on the intended audience. The children will be looking at the importance of using a range of sources and how to analyse a wide range of evidence to justify their claims. We will be producing artwork based around the theme of propaganda and designing posters using a range of techniques.&nbsp;</font></p><p class="p1"><font face="arial" color="#3366ff"><b>Computing</b></font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">In computing, the children will be finishing their unit on google sheets. This will involve creating simple and complex formulas, working with functions, sorting and filtering data and the different types of cells and references. We will then be looking at youtube creator where the children will learn how to create and share videos, how to upload tools and edit their work and they will then have the chance to publish their own video. In design and technology we will focus on ‘people in action’. We will look at proportion of people when sketching and how we can portray movement. We will combine everything we have learnt and make a flip book to show an olympic event.&nbsp;</span></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255); font-size: 12pt;">Physical Education (PE)</b></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">In PE, Year 6 children will have two one-hour PE lessons (Mondays and Wednesdays) and one separate swimming lesson (Thursdays). On their swimming lesson day, they will come in their school uniform, not PE kit. &nbsp;On their PE days, they will come in PE kit and remain in it for the whole day. In their PE lessons, over the course of Term 3, the Year 6 children will take part in some of the following activities: tag rugby, athletics, striking and fielding games, unihoc, badminton, dance, games making, gymnastics and OAA (Outdoor and Adventurous Activities). &nbsp;These activities will be rotated throughout the term, so that by the end of Term 3, all groups will have completed all the PE activities on the Year 6 PE Curriculum, across the academic year. &nbsp;The children will continue to be grouped by ability and will be assessed throughout the term, in order that we can move pupils accordingly.</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255); font-size: 12pt;">Modern Foreign Languages (MFL)</b></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">Year 6 children have the option to study either Mandarin or Spanish. Both Mandarin and Spanish &nbsp;lessons are differentiated by ability due to the range of competency amongst our children.&nbsp;</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b style="font-size: 12pt;">Mandarin</b></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">In Term 3 the Mandarin lessons in Year 6 for beginner level will be covering the topics of “Animals”, “Colours”, “Adjectives and Body Parts” and “Countries and Languages”.</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">Elementary level will be covering the topics of “Weather”, “School timetable” and “Stationery”. Intermediate level will be covering the topics of “Leisure time”, “The Animals in the Zoo” and “Living Environment”.&nbsp;</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">Advanced level will be focus on the passage, “<i>Xin Xue Qi De Di Yi Tian</i>” (The First Day of School) and “<i>Ma Ma Xing Fu De Xiao Le</i>” (Mummy is Smiling Happily) and “<i>Ge Ge Zhang De Hen Gao</i>” (Elder Brother is Very Tall).&nbsp;</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">All levels will continue to develop children's listening, speaking, reading and writing skills.</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b style="font-size: 12pt;">Spanish</b></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">The Year 6 Spanish group will be covering a number of short topics this term including:- <i>The Cafe, Shopping at the Market, Hobbies and Sports, &nbsp;My School and Clothes and My Body</i>. The children will be learning through creative activities, games, songs and stories. They will be encouraged to give their opinions and reasons and say what they like and dislike to develop their fluency and confidence. The topics will also enable the children to develop their grammar and use of verbs and adjectives. The children will also be preparing to perform in the Spanish assembly in the third term.</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255); font-size: 12pt;">Music</b></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">In music this term the children will be looking at the following topics:</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial"><b>Who Knows?: Exploring Musical Processes</b></font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">This topic will look at different starting points as inspiration for creating music, including silent movies and cartoons. The children will then develop their own silent movie sketch, which they will then create music to accompany.</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b style="font-size: 12pt;">Class Band: Performing Together</b></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">Each class will work together to choose a song from a range of material and create their own arrangement. They will need to decide on instrumentation, arrangement as well as honing their performance skills, culminating in a live concert.</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255); font-size: 12pt;">Homework</b></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">In Year 6, we encourage more independent work in preparation for the transition to secondary school. Children will be given two weekly 40-minute homework tasks linked to literacy (including topic) work or mathematics from their class teacher, as well as specialist homework for Modern Foreign Languages. Spelling homework, comprising sentence work or investigations, must be handed in on a Friday. For maths homework, we will be using <i>Mymaths</i> and a range of mathematics activities complementing the work carried out in class. This will be set on a Wednesday, to be completed by the following Wednesday. The children will also receive weekly homework from their Modern Foreign Language (MFL) – Spanish, Mandarin or Bahasa class.</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255); font-size: 12pt;">Communication</b></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">Each Year 6 class will continue to share with you what is happening in class via the class portal blogs. Any changes to normal school routine or important dates/events will be shared via the school calendar. Although a notification e-mail may be sent, we encourage parents to check the Parent Portal calendar regularly.</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">For safeguarding purposes, we ask that adults wear their identification tags at all times within school and if your child is due to be collected by someone else, please do inform us in advance.</span></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Events to look forward to this term:</span></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">21st April -&nbsp;Year 6 End of KS2 Assessment Meeting&nbsp;</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">29th April<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span>-&nbsp;Open Morning</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">5th May -&nbsp;Year 6 Sports Day</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">1st June -&nbsp;Pupil led conferences</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">24th June<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span>&nbsp;- Year 6 Transition Day</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">1st July -&nbsp;International Day (children to dress up)</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">11th July - Year 6 Graduation</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">12th July -&nbsp;Hari Raya Celebration Day (children to dress up)</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">We hope you find this information useful and I am sure that this is going to be a very positive and productive Year 6. As always, if you have any questions or concerns please contact your class teacher as a first point of contact.</span></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">&nbsp;</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">Kind regards,&nbsp;</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial"><b>Year 6 Team</b></font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial"><b>Craig Moore (Year 6 leader) &amp; Ms Alison Lazenby &nbsp;&nbsp;</b></font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">craig.moore@britishschool.edu.my</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial"><b>James Dallas &amp; Ms Abbie O’Neill &nbsp; </b>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">james.dallas@britishschool.edu.my</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial"><b>Kayleigh Smith &amp; Mr Phil Leama</b>n &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">kayleigh.smith@britishschool.edu.my</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial"><b>Tom Kimber &amp; Ms Imogen Allan &nbsp; &nbsp; </b>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">thomas.kimber@britishschool.edu.my</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial"><b>Jessica Weaire &amp; Mr Michael Bradley &nbsp; &nbsp;</b> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial"><span class="s1"></span></font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">jessica.weaire@britishschool.edu.my</font></p><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><br></div>
